### Test Simple del Servidor MCP

### 1. Verificar si el servidor responde a HTTP básico
GET http://localhost:8970

### 2. Probar con método simple
POST http://localhost:8970
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": "test-1",
  "method": "ping",
  "params": {}
}

### 3. Probar con método que sabemos que existe
POST http://localhost:8970
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": "test-2",
  "method": "initialize",
  "params": {
    "protocolVersion": "2024-11-05",
    "capabilities": {},
    "clientInfo": {
      "name": "TestClient",
      "version": "1.0.0"
    }
  }
}

### 4. Verificar si hay algún endpoint específico
GET http://localhost:8970/health
GET http://localhost:8970/status
GET http://localhost:8970/info

